[quoted lines by Andrew Park on February 28, 2000, at 12:03]
>I get an odd NFS behaviour.  Let's say I have my home directory mapped at
>/nfssrv/home, then I would see all my subdirectories under /nfssrv/home, but
>when I 'cd' into one of the sub-directories (i.e. /nfssrv/home/src) and do an
>'ls' it shows nothing.  
I've seen that happen when the rsize option of the mount is low and the number
of files in the directory is large. Increasing rsize seems to fix the problem.
